
# x48

Original README is [here](doc/README).

If all goes well, simply running **[./fedora.sh](fedora.sh)** should build and install the x48 rpm, copy ROMs to **~/.hp48**,
and initialize the app.  If other users want to use the app or the rpm fails to install then these key lines from the script
must be manually run:

    mkdir -p ~/.hp48
    cp -av ROMs/*  ~/.hp48
    ( cd  ~/.hp48 && ln -svf gxrom-r rom && ln -svf rom rom.dump &&  if [ !  -s hp48 ] ;  then x48 -initialize ;  fi )

The default rom is **gxrom-r**; another good choice is **sxrom-j**.
